{"id":22642,"date":"2024-01-23T09:39:00","date_gmt":"2024-01-23T04:09:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=22642"},"modified":"2024-03-11T10:21:25","modified_gmt":"2024-03-11T04:51:25","slug":"vastu-for-home-office","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/vastu-for-home-office\/","title":{"rendered":"Vastu For Home Office: Make Your Work From Home Experience Work For You"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><em>Vastu tips to make your home office a productive space<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Post pandemic, the lines between home and office have blurred. When everyone had to resort to working from home in 2021, little did anyone anticipate that this way of working might become a more permanent thing for the years to come.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>For jobs and businesses that can successfully run from the comfort of your homes, it is vital to ensure that:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>You create zones or spaces within the house that separate your work life and personal life; this means that working from your bed is a strict no-no, for example; and<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Your <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/interior-design\/home-office-design\/\">home office interior<\/a> is a positive and productive zone where work actually gets done consistently and without any hindrances.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1842\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/07\/25150638\/vastu-tips-to-make-your-home-office-productive-space-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"Vastu tips to make your home office a productive space\" class=\"wp-image-36279\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/07\/25150638\/vastu-tips-to-make-your-home-office-productive-space-scaled.jpg 1842w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/07\/25150638\/vastu-tips-to-make-your-home-office-productive-space-216x300.